Madison County Soil & Water Conservation District
September 27, 2019 at 12:54 PM ·

NRCS Soil Health Specialist Doug Peterson (with the help of I-35 students) demonstrated the aggregate stability test (aka slake test) at the Soil Health Workshop in Winterset on September 24, 2019.

This demonstration shows how management plays a key role in the aggregate stability of soils (these were the same soil type). The difference is management: conventional tillage (left) vs. long-term no-till (right).

RED BRAND RENEWS THE FFA WILDFIRE RELIEF CHALLENGE - Drought conditions this spring have once again caused significant loss of property, cattle and even human life due to wildfires in Oklahoma. Over 350,000 acres of grazing and pasture land have burned, destroying miles of fence.

We are ready to help support the recovery efforts by launching the 2018 FFA Red Brand Wildfire Relief Challenge. Established in 2016, this initiative encourages FFA Chapters to lend a hand to neighbors and communities (near or far) in need of manpower for fence tear-out or rebuilding. In return, Red Brand will donate up to $500 to the FFA Chapter. For information about the challenge, please click here: http://www.redbrand.com/WildFire.aspx.

post_text: We need moisture and BTUs!
shared_text:
Nutrients for Life Foundation
April 13, 2018 at 1:02 PM ·

Since it's the middle of April, and very few acres have been planted in the Midwest, here are some facts about soil temperatures that might help to explain the delay in planting.

Corn requires a soil temperature of 50° F to germinate and grow and soybeans require a soil temperature of 54° F. Temperatures below the optimum can cause seeds to sit dormant and become more vulnerable to diseases, insects, and animal predators.
#FertilizerFriday, #winterneedstoend

Do you know of a high school senior graduating this spring who plans to pursue studies in conservation or agriculture? Let them know about this scholarship opportunity through Conservation Districts of Iowa!

Applications are due to your local SWCD office by Friday, February 16.

The Conservation Scholarship Winner from CDI's Region 6 (that includes Madison County!) will receive an additional $350 from the Larry Beeler Memorial Scholarship Fund.

Larry Beeler was a SWCD Commissioner in Madison County, and this is the final year the memorial scholarship will be offered, so it would be great to have applications from students in Madison County!

For more information, visit CDI's website:
http://cdiowa.org/conservation-districts-of-iowa/programs/public-education-acknowledgment/scholarships

Interstate Graduate and FFA supporter, Jenna Sandquist had a dream to study Global Resource Systems at Iowa State and travel to learn. She did so by going to China as an intern for Cargill. Jenna achieved her dream! Now onto the next!

"I’m very excited to announce that I have recently accepted an offer to join Cargill full-time after graduation! I won’t be moving all the way to China this time, but we will be making a small move up to the Minneapolis area. In Wayzata, I will begin a rotational Supply Chain Associate program!"
